nvmultiurisrcbin integrates REST API and the API at
gst-nvmultiurisrcbincreator.h to support runtime source addition and deletion.

Note: This bin is an Alpha release. Support might be limited.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install OpenTelemetry dependencies
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Enter the following commands to install OpenTelemetry:

$ cd ~
$ mkdir otel_src && cd otel_src && git clone --branch v1.23.0 --recurse-submodules https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-cpp
$ cd opentelemetry-cpp
$ mkdir build && cd build
$ sudo apt install cmake
$ cmake .. -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON -DWITH_OTLP_GRPC=ON -DWITH_OTLP_HTTP=ON
$ cmake --build . --parallel $(nproc)
$ ctest -V (Optional: run tests for verification)
$ sudo cmake --install .

For more information, refer to the OpenTelemetry C++ installation guide:
https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-cpp/blob/v1.23.0/INSTALL.md

Note: After installing OpenTelemetry, clear gstreamer cache and run ldconfig command.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Installing Pre-requisites:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Packages to be installed:
$ sudo apt install \
    libssl3 \
    libssl-dev \
    libgles2-mesa-dev \
    libgstrtspserver-1.0-0 \
    libjansson4 \
    libyaml-cpp-dev \
    libjsoncpp-dev \
    libcurl4-openssl-dev

Compiling and installing the plugin:
Export or set in Makefile the appropriate CUDA_VER
Run make and sudo make install

NOTE: To compile the sources, run make with "sudo" or root permission.
